Build without itstool/xsltproc (docs).

Two unconditional bits of the build need tools we do not ship: data/meson.build
runs the appstreamcli metainfo through itstool (which needs python libxml2
bindings), and the docs subdir renders man pages from DocBook via xsltproc,
which then tries to fetch the DocBook XSL stylesheet over the network. Neither
the metainfo nor the man pages matter to our consumers (libadwaita /
gnome-control-center link libappstream), so install the untranslated metainfo
and drop the docs subdir. Mirrors the man/docs-off choice used across the tree.

--- a/meson.build
+++ b/meson.build
@@ -207,7 +207,6 @@
 subdir('po/')
 subdir('data/')
 subdir('contrib/')
-subdir('docs/')
 subdir('tests/')
 if get_option('qt')
     subdir('qt/')
--- a/data/meson.build
+++ b/data/meson.build
@@ -17,11 +17,12 @@
     command : [ascli_exe, 'news-to-metainfo', '--limit=6', '@INPUT0@', '@INPUT1@', '@OUTPUT@']
 )
 
-metainfo_i18n = i18n.itstool_join(
-    input:  metainfo_with_relinfo,
+# itstool is not available in this build; install the untranslated metainfo
+# for the appstreamcli tool instead of running itstool_join over it.
+metainfo_i18n = custom_target('cli-metainfo',
+    input: metainfo_with_relinfo,
     output: 'org.freedesktop.appstream.cli.metainfo.xml',
-    mo_targets: i18n_result[0],
-    its_files: [join_paths(meson.current_source_dir(), 'its', 'metainfo.its')],
+    command: ['cp', '@INPUT@', '@OUTPUT@'],
     install: true,
     install_dir: metainfo_dir,
 )
